  "name": "Scintillating Spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your spells become a radiant display of light and color.</p>\n<p>If your next action is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} that doesn't have the darkness trait, has no duration, and requires creatures to attempt a Reflex save, the spell explodes in a spray of scintillating lights, in addition to its other effects.</p>\n<p>Each creature that failed its Reflex save against the spell is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TkIyaNPgTZFBCCuh]{Dazzled} for 1 round, and those who critically failed are instead @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.XgEqL1kFApUbl5Z2]{Blinded} for 1 round.</p>"
